gner by applying with a creditworthy cosigner you may improve your likelihood for loan approval and may receive a lower interest rate  what is the difference between a fixed interest rate and variable interest rate a fixed interest rate is set during the time of application and does not change during the life of the loan a variable interest rate may change quarterly during the life of the loan if the month libor changes this may cause the monthly payment to increase the number of payments to increase or both  what is the  cash rewards for good grades doing your homework has its rewards get at least a  gpa or equivalent and receive a onetime cash reward of  of the loan amount of each new discover student loan applicable for eligible loan applications submitted on or after may   reward redemption period is limited learn more  what is an auto debit reward get a  interest rate reduction when you are enrolled in automatic payments during repayment to enroll for automatic payments complete the enrollment form online or call us at student to request a copy of the enrollment form complete it and mail it back to the address on the form learn more undergraduate loan repayment  what is a deferment period if you are in school at least halftime on active military duty serving a public service organization or in a medical residency you may qualify for a deferment a deferment period is a period of time when a borrower is not required to make any payments during deferment interest will continue to accrue at the end of a deferment period any unpaid interest will be added to your principal balance this may increase the amount of your monthly payments and the total cost of your loans learn more  what is my repayment period a repayment period is the period of time during which scheduled payments are required to be made to repay the principal balance and interest on a loan your repayment period is  years after the deferment period ends  what are my repayment options inschool  required to make  fixed monthly payments while you are inschool and during your grace period to lower your overall loan cost deferred  monthly payments are not required until  months after you graduate or your enrollment drops below halftime you can make payments anytime to help reduce the overall cost of your loan and there is never a penalty for prepaying if youre not receiving monthly billing statements we will send you quarterly statements showing you how much interest is accruing and how to make optional payments while you are in school  what if i need help making my monthly payments if you are experiencing financial difficulties and you are unable to make your student loan payments we have options to help to learn more and determine if you qualify please call our repayment assistance department at student learn more student loan resources for students and parents previous types of financial aid learn about the different types financial aid  learn more navigating financial aid find out more about the financial aid process and how to pay for college  learn more does it pay to stay instate compare undergraduate tuition by state  learn more scholarship tips its never too early for undergraduates to start researching scholarships  learn more how to reduce tuition costs  tips to help keep your tuition costs down  learn more early decision vs early action here are some things undergraduate students should consider when applying early  learn more next find college scholarships frequently asked questions sign up for tips  advice home pay for college overviewfor pay for college financial aid college loans about college for parents scholarships private student loans overviewfor private student loans undergraduate loans graduate loans mba loans health professions loans law loans residency loans bar exam loans consolidation loans pay your loans overviewfor pay your loans repayment basics rewards student loan calculators overviewfor student loan calculators award letter comparison st