deferment interest will continue to accrue at the end of a deferment period any unpaid interest will be added to your principal balance this may increase the amount of your monthly payments and the total cost of your loans learn more  what is my repayment period a repayment period is the period of time during which scheduled payments are required to be made to repay the principal balance and interest on a loan your repayment period is  years after the deferment period ends  what are my repayment options inschool  required to make  fixed monthly payments while you are inschool and during your grace period to lower your overall loan cost deferred  monthly payments are not required until  months after you graduate or your enrollment drops below halftime you can make payments anytime to help reduce the overall cost of your loan and there is never a penalty for prepaying if youre not receiving monthly billing statements we will send you quarterly statements showing you how much interest is accruing and how to make optional payments while you are in school  what if i need help making my monthly payments if you are experiencing financial difficulties and you are unable to make your student loan payments we have options to help to learn more and determine if you qualify please call our repayment assistance department at student learn more student loan resources for students and parents previous types of financial aid learn about the different types financial aid  learn more navigating financial aid find out more about the financial aid process and how to pay for college  learn more does it pay to stay instate compare undergraduate tuition by state  learn more scholarship tips its never too early for undergraduates to start researching scholarships  learn more how to reduce tuition costs  tips to help keep your tuition costs down  learn more early decision vs early action here are some things undergraduate students should consider when applying early  learn more next find co